saleyards
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a set of yards and pens used for the purposes of stock auctions  [owned either by a local authority or sale agencies.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:also saleyard
